---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Fangzhou Jiang" description="A bit more about who I am and what I'm looking for.">
  <div class="about">
    <h1>About Me</h1>

    <section class="section">
      <p>
        I'm Fangzhou, a software engineer based in London, Ontario. I build LLM-powered
        systems — multi-agent pipelines, retrieval systems, and the evaluation infrastructure
        that makes the difference between a cool demo and something that actually works in
        production.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm currently completing my Master's in Computer Science at Western University. Before
        that, I spent 3 years as a Software Engineer in Test at Netease Games in Shanghai,
        where I built test automation platforms and performance testing infrastructure for
        large-scale distributed game servers — including Marvel Rivals and Dead by Daylight
        Mobile.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>How I got here</h2>
      <p>
        My background is in software engineering in test and backend development — I spent
        years as a Software Engineer in Test at Netease, stress testing game servers at scale,
        profiling performance bottlenecks, and building internal backend systems and tooling.
        The shift toward LLM systems was a natural extension: I started applying them to
        automate test workflows at Netease, then kept going after seeing how much engineering
        work goes into making them reliable enough to actually use.
      </p>
      <p>
        At Western I've been researching AI-driven procedural content generation in games —
        specifically what it takes to make LLM output fast and stable enough to work inside
        a real-time game loop.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What I'm looking for</h2>
      <p>
        I'm most effective on small, high-trust teams where engineers own problems end-to-end —
        from defining what to measure to shipping the thing that improves the metric. I like
        working close to the product, not just the infrastructure.
      </p>
      <p>
        The problems I find most interesting right now: making LLM outputs reliably evaluable,
        building systems that degrade gracefully when the model is wrong, and the practical
        engineering of retrieval at scale.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Outside work</h2>
      <p>
        I build games on the side — mostly Unity projects where I can implement algorithms I
        find interesting (procedural generation, pathfinding, AI behaviour) without the
        pressure of a production codebase.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section contact-section">
      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Best way to reach me is email:
        <a href="mailto:jiangfz1997@gmail.com">jiangfz1997@gmail.com</a>.
        I'm also on <a href="https://github.com/jiangfz1997" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
        and on <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/fangzhou-jiang/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }

  h1 {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .section h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .section p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .contact-section p {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
</style>
